        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 10 at 1:46PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 145 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Quintana, or near Refugio. This thunderstorm was drifting
southeast.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Refugio, Woodsboro, and Quintana.

This includes the following highways...
US Highway 183 between mile markers 662 and 668.
US Highway 77 between mile markers 602 and 626.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
